    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-04T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-04T10:00:00-05:00" n="183"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d183">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 <gloss target="#t_EW1">EW</gloss>/7–445:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 183 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative to the International Conference on Military
                        Trials</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_JRH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jackson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d183fn1">Sent over the signature of <persName
                            corresp="#p_WJG2">Winant</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extracts]<note n="2" xml:id="d183fn2">For a summary of
                            the substantive portions of this message, see <ref target="#d395"
                                >document No. 395</ref>.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-04T17:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 4, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6729. Top secret for Secretary <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName> from
                        <persName corresp="#p_JRH1">Justice Jackson</persName>.</p>
                <p>Your cable 5383, July 3.<note n="3" xml:id="d183fn3">Not printed.</note>
                    Negotiations of agreement trial principal war criminals progressing slowly due
                    difficulty Russian understanding our system of law and our difficulty
                    comprehending theirs. …</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Am rather appalled at thought of Big Three trying to discuss subject so technical
                    and involved and one where details so important. Mr. <pb facs="0354" n="222"
                        xml:id="pg_222"/>
                    <persName corresp="#p_DP1">Dean</persName> of British Foreign Office explains
                    British suggestions<note n="4" xml:id="d183fn4">See <ref target="#d176">document
                            No. 176</ref>.</note> as not intending detailed discussion but rather as
                    intended to allay Russian suspicion that prosecution is being evaded.</p>
                <p>If Big Three undertake discussion seems important that I review matter in some
                    detail President and you because important differences lurk in small phrases.
                    …</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
